Bubble Temperature Analysis: Late November 2021 - December 2024¶

The Data Sets¶

Data sets were derived from WQData Live. Temperature data from November 2021 - March 2023 was measured using the X2 Legacy: X2-01123: [2] CTD Temp. Temperature data from March 2023 - December 2024 was measured using the X2 Legacy: X2-01123: EXO Temp. There is a small gap in the temperature data between March 20 2023 - March ___ 2023.

raw_df_2024 = pd.read_csv('/Users/miaaaronson/Desktop/ENE390/Thesis_Work/Data/ALL_BUBBLE_DATA_2024.csv')
raw_df_2023 = pd.read_csv('/Users/miaaaronson/Desktop/ENE390/Thesis_Work/Data/ALL_BUBBLE_DATA_2023.csv')
raw_df_2021to032023 = pd.read_csv('/Users/miaaaronson/Desktop/ENE390/Thesis_Work/Data/ALL_BUBBLE_TEMPS_2021to03:2023 2.csv')

def clean_water_data(raw_df):
    # Consolidate relevant data by selecting specific columns
    df = raw_df[
        [
            "Site",
            "X2",
            "X2.1",
            "X2.2",
            "X2.3",
            "X2.4",
        ]
    ]
    
    # Set the second row as column headers
    df.columns = df.iloc[1]
    
    # Remove the first two rows and reset index
    df = df[2:].reset_index(drop=True)
    
    # Convert column names to a list for manipulation
    column_names = df.columns.to_list()
    
    # Rename specific NaN columns
    column_names[0] = "Time and Date"
    column_names[3] = "pH Value"
    
    # Set updated column names back to DataFrame
    df.columns = column_names
    
    # Rename other columns for clarity
    df.rename(
        columns={
            "C": "Temperature (C)",
            "uS/cm": "Specific Conductivity (uS/cm)",
            "%": "ODO (Saturation)",
            "mg/L": "ODO (mg/L)",
        },
        inplace=True,
    )
    
    # Drop rows where Temperature in Degrees C is NaN
    df = df.dropna(subset=["Temperature (C)"])
    
    # Convert columns to appropriate data types
    df["Time and Date"] = pd.to_datetime(df["Time and Date"], format="%m-%d-%Y %H:%M:%S")
    df["Temperature (C)"] = pd.to_numeric(df["Temperature (C)"], errors="coerce")
    
    return df

final_2021on = raw_df_2021to032023.iloc[2:]
final_2021on = final_2021on.dropna()
final_2021on.rename(columns={'C': 'Temperature (C)'}, inplace=True)

# smoothing methods
from statsmodels.tsa.holtwinters import ExponentialSmoothing
from scipy import signal
from statsmodels.nonparametric.smoothers_lowess import lowess
import matplotlib.dates as mdates

# exponential smoothing
exponential_smoothing_model = ExponentialSmoothing(
    y_p3, trend=None, seasonal=None, damped_trend=False
)
fit_model = exponential_smoothing_model.fit()
y_smooth_es = fit_model.predict(
    start=len(y_p3), end=len(y_p3)
)
y_smooth_es = fit_model.fittedvalues

# moving average
y_smooth_ma = y_p3.rolling(window=500, center=True).mean()

# SGF
y_smooth_SGF = signal.savgol_filter(y_p3, window_length=150, polyorder=3, mode="nearest")

# lowess
max_threshold_3 = 13.3
min_threshold_3 = 13
all_temp_data_for_lowess = all_temp_data[(all_temp_data["Temperature (C)"] > min_threshold_3) &
                        (all_temp_data["Temperature (C)"] < max_threshold_3)]
x_dates = all_temp_data_for_lowess.index
x_numeric = mdates.date2num(x_dates)
smoothed = lowess(all_temp_data_for_lowess['Temperature (C)'], all_temp_data_for_lowess.index, frac=0.05)


# Plotting
fig, axs = plt.subplots(5,1, figsize=(16,8))

# raw data graph
axs[0].plot(x_p3, y_p3, label="Raw Data", color="#7393B3")
axs[0].set_title("Data Smoothing: Raw Data")
axs[0].legend()

# ES graph
axs[1].plot(x_p3, y_p3, label="Raw Data", color="#BCD2E8")
axs[1].plot(x_p3, y_smooth_es, label="Smoothed Data", color="#0818A8")
axs[1].set_title("Data Smoothing:Exponential Smoothing Method")
axs[1].legend()

# MS graph
axs[2].plot(x_p3, y_p3, label="Raw Data", color="#BCD2E8")
axs[2].plot(x_p3, y_smooth_ma, label="Smoothed Data", color="#0818A8")
axs[2].set_title("Data Smoothing: Moving Average Smoothing Method")
axs[2].legend()

axs[3].plot(x_p3, y_p3, label="Raw Data", color="#BCD2E8")
axs[3].plot(smoothed[:, 1], label="Smoothed Values", color="#0818A8")
axs[3].set_title("Data Smoothing: Lowess Smoothing Method")
axs[3].legend()

# SGF graph
axs[4].plot(x_p3, y_p3, label="Raw Data", color="#BCD2E8")
axs[4].plot(x_p3, y_smooth_SGF, label="Smoothed Data", color="#0818A8")
axs[4].set_title("Data Smoothing Savitzky-Golay Filtering Smoothing Method")
axs[4].legend()

plt.subplots_adjust(hspace=1)

# Compute time differences in seconds
x_all = pd.to_datetime(x_all)  # Ensure correct datetime format
time_diffs = np.diff(x_all).astype('timedelta64[s]').astype(float)

# Compute average sampling interval
sampling_interval = np.mean(time_diffs)  # seconds per sample
sampling_rate = 1 / sampling_interval  # Hz

# Apply FFT with zero-padding for finer resolution
N = len(y_smooth)  # Use original data (or y_total_smoothed if preferred)
fft_values = np.fft.fft(y_all, n=N)

# Compute frequencies
frequencies = np.fft.fftfreq(N, d=sampling_interval)

signal = y_all  # or y_smooth

# FFT
fft_values = np.fft.fft(signal, n=len(signal))
frequencies = np.fft.fftfreq(len(signal), d=sampling_interval)

# Now find the dominant frequency
positive_freqs = frequencies[:len(signal)//2]
positive_fft = np.abs(fft_values[:len(signal)//2])

# Skip the 0 Hz point
dominant_idx = np.argmax(positive_fft[1:]) + 1
dominant_freq = positive_freqs[dominant_idx]
period_seconds = 1 / dominant_freq
period_days = period_seconds / (3600 * 24)

print(f"Dominant period ≈ {period_days:.2f} days")

fig, axs = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(16, 8))

# Plot FFT Spectrum (Magnitude)
axs[1].plot(frequencies[:N//2], np.abs(fft_values[:N//2]))  # Only positive frequencies
axs[1].set_xlabel("Frequency (Hz)")
axs[1].set_ylabel("Magnitude")
axs[1].set_title("FFT of Temperature Data at Bubble")# Log scale helps reveal smaller frequencies
axs[1].set_yscale('log')

axs[0].plot(frequencies[:N//2], np.abs(fft_values[:N//2]))  # Only positive frequencies
axs[0].set_xlabel("Frequency (Hz)")
axs[0].set_ylabel("Magnitude")
axs[0].set_title("FFT of Temperature Data at Bubble")# Log scale helps reveal smaller frequencies

plt.axvline(x=dominant_freq, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"~{period_days:.0f}-day cycle")
plt.legend()
plt.subplots_adjust(hspace=.3)

plt.show()

Dominant period ≈ 94.17 days
